definition: name/noun (part of speech)/place (e.g. among winners)/famous/classifier for people

sentences.english: So why is the humble chair being blacklisted?
sentences.chinese: 但爲什麼這次是“老實巴交”的椅子被列入黑名單呢？
簽發和管理授權人員名單。

sentences.english: Her name was dropped from the list.
sentences.chinese: 她的名字已從名單上除去了。

sentences.english: He took to safe that removed the list.
sentences.chinese: 他帶着曉陽去保險櫃裏取出了名單。

sentences.english: You may also forward us a list of qualified drivers from your respective countries for our reference.
sentences.chinese: 你也可以自貴國傳一份合格選手的名單給我們參考。

sentences.english: The names of the members of the team will be posted up today.
sentences.chinese: 隊員名單將於今天張榜公佈。

sentences.english: Every year we gaze enviously at the lists of the richest people in world.
sentences.chinese: 每一年我們羨慕地盯着世界上最有錢的人名單。

sentences.english: They checked to see if she enrolled among the voters of their district.
sentences.chinese: 他們複覈看看她是否被登記在他們區的選民名單中。

sentences.english: However, only the wrong routing alarm was included on the short-list.
sentences.chinese: 然而，只有錯誤的路由警報是列入名單。

sentences.english: The U.S.' overall EPI score is 81, putting it in 39th place on the list.
sentences.chinese: 美國的EPI綜合分數爲81，在名單中排在39位。

sentences.english: Take those keywords and add them to your preliminary list.
sentences.chinese: 把這些關鍵字都加入到你的候選名單中去。

sentences.english: He's been wait-listed for a football scholarship to Stanford .
sentences.chinese: 他已被列入斯坦福大學的美式足球獎學金等候者名單。

sentences.english: Contraste Bar features a range of tapas paired with cocktails and an international beer list.
sentences.chinese: 對比各種tapas搭配雞尾酒和國際啤酒名單。

sentences.english: And this president has even approved names of American citizens on that list.
sentences.chinese: 而且這個大總統甚至把一些美國公民也列入名單。

sentences.english: Report the examined and approved qualified suppliers list of this project to company for record.
sentences.chinese: 將本項目審定合格的供貨商名單報公司備案。

definition: auxiliary verb introducing future action: may (be able to)/will (cause)/should (enable)/going to
